### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It will handle routing for all nine pages, process user inputs, read/write data from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and render the corresponding HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, consolidating backend logic into this single file is efficient and maintainable.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web application pages, each corresponding to one of the nine pages specified in the requirements. These templates will include the defined elements with their respective IDs for frontend rendering and interaction.

  - `dashboard.html` — Dashboard page with featured vehicles, promotions, and navigation buttons.  
